  "texts": [
    "While most of the current research is devoted to desktop applications, there exist other use cases which may not fit in this field.",
    "For instance, (Qian et al. 2021) integrated a custom eyetracking system in an MRI scanner, whereas Katrychuk et al. (2019) checked DL networks with different capacities to be integrated into a Raspberry Pi 3.",
    "In conclusion, there is no better technique regarding efficiency for every possible scenario; computer vision pipelines are typically fast enough due to the low dimensionality of IR images, especially in feature-based methods.",
    "Machine learning offers, on the other hand, low latency while having higher memory requirements, although this depends on the number of trained weights.",
    "Otherwise, it is possible to develop shallow CNN with few parameters that are still able to recognize high-level features."
